news.title: Signature Global reports 113.92% growth in pre-sales at Rs 879.78 crore in Q1 FY24
news.para: Signature Global reported 64.92% growth in collections at Rs 1,327.45 crore in H1 FY24 while its sales realization grew to approximately Rs 9,800 per sq. ft. from about Rs 7,425 per sq. ft. in H1 FY23.

news.title: Shalimar Paints looks to invest Rs 200 crore in two years
news.para: “We are being very, very careful with where we spend. So within this Rs 200 crore, we have already drawn out the plan, most of the ordering also has been done and execution has started,” said Ashok Gupta, MD & CEO, Shalimar Paints.

news.title: New office space supply across top seven cities to exceed 165 million sq ft between 2023-2025: Report
news.para: Between 2023-2025, Bengaluru will lead the office space supply, accounting for 29% of the total supply in India, followed by Hyderabad at 20%, Delhi-NCR at 17%, Pune at 12%, Chennai at 11%, Mumbai at 9% and Kolkata at 2%.

news.title: Push for planned construction: Himachal Pradesh chief secretary
news.para: To save precious human lives, compliance of the rules of the Urban and Town Planning Act would be ensured and planned construction works would be promoted, he added.

news.title: YEIDA announces group housing plot scheme for Greater Noida
news.para: There will be an allocation of land for a total of six types of plots in Sector 22-D of Greater Noida, and bidding worth crores for this will take place on November 21.

news.title: Bokaro Steel Plant to raze over 100 houses on October 12
news.para: This locality is the same where recently squatters launched an attack on the BSL anti-encroachment team when it went to remove a concrete structure coming up illegally close to the Sector 4 police station.

news.title: CAG raps TNUHDB, CMDA for construction on water body
news.para: It also highlighted that the Chennai Metropolitan Development Authority’s (CMDA) reclassification of water bodies for residential use can cause environmental damage.

news.title: Cabinet decides to amend Shimla development plan
news.para: Residential construction in the green belt areas as per the Shimla Development Plan, however, will be permitted only on those plots in which there are no trees.

news.title: Gujarat RERA asks developers to comply with queries in time
news.para: Senior officers in RERA said that currently, around 200 project registrations are pending just because developers have not responded to queries raised by the authority.

news.title: Mohali development body's Eco City project hits CMO roadblock
news.para: GMADA was to acquire land for Urban Estate Eco City-3 in New Chandigarh. The authority was set to acquire 720 acres for the project, and was awaiting the CM’s nod.

news.title: CAG slams TNUHDB delay in building houses under central scheme
news.para: The performance audit for the year ended March 31, 2021, tabled in the assembly, said against the total housing demand of 13.92 lakh, the TNUHDB obtained sanction for only 7.08 lakh houses during 2015-21.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Property tax leviable for paid parking
news.para: The policy says property tax won’t be levied on spaces in residential properties or commercial properties where parking is free.

news.title: NGT bars leasing of plot next to Navi Mumbai creek for development
news.para: Two applications, filed by the Navi Mumbai Environment Preservation Society (NMEPS) and a group of six city residents, sought that Cidco be stopped from going ahead with the auction. The base price had been fixed at Rs 1.4 lakh per sq m.

news.title: Property registrations up, Noida to add two more sub-registrar offices
news.para: “The revenue department has submitted a proposal to open two more sub-registrar offices in Greater Noida and Dadri. The objective behind this initiative is to alleviate the burden on existing offices and expedite property registration procedures,” Mishra said.

news.title: Act against SHO, court tells Gurugram police commissioner, calls officer 'incompetent'
news.para: The sessions court in 2022 dismissed a challenge against the trial and directed police in May to issue summons to the directors of Precision Realtors, Madeira Conbuild, Global Estate and Ireo Grace Realtech – all of which were involved in the project.

news.title: Check SRA potential at government colony in Bandra East: Maharashtra CM
news.para: Shinde added that after studying the site of the SRA in the government colony, its capacity and all technical aspects, including the funnel zone, a decision on redevelopment will be taken.

news.title: Supreme Court rejects bail plea of ex-promoter of AN Buidwell
news.para: A bench of justices Aniruddha Bose and Bela M Trivedi on October 4 dismissed the plea of Surendra Kumar Hooda, ex-promoters and directors of real estate company AN Buidwell.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body appoints special team for survey of dangerous structures
news.para: In a recent tragic incident in Dombivli city, one dangerous building collapsed, resulting in the loss of two lives and one person being injured.
